   @{FG shine}------------------
      INTRODUCTION
  --------------------@{FG text}


   For a long time  I was using Win95 taskbar clone. The  thing that bored
 me was a lot of clicking with mouse (click on 'start', then on 'programs'
 then on 'disk', then on..). The solution was ToolManager which used a lot
 of space on screen (for every executable one button) and when i put about
 50 programs on dock i couldn`t see my beautiful Workbench. Then i decided
 to create an utility which wont need much clicking and wont take too much
 space on screen, so i created MaxMenu.


   @{FG shine}------------------
      REQUIREMENTS
  --------------------@{FG text}


   - Amiga :)

   - KS 2.x or greater (I think)

   - ReqTools.library - by Nico Francois (included)

   - ScreenNotify.library - by Stefan Becker (included)

   - WBStart.library 2.2+ - by Stefan Becker (included)
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Introduction"

   @{FG shine}------------------
      INSTALLATION
  --------------------@{FG text}


   Installation of  MaxMenu is very  simple - just start  the installation
 script that  I have included in  this archive. If  you want to install it
 all by  yourself then  copy the contents  of drawers Prefs, WbStartup and
 Libs to  their equivalents  in SYS: partition.

   If you are upgrading from previous version of MaxMenu you have to start
 ConfigConvert program to convert your old MaxMenu configuration.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "ToDo"
@prev "Installation"

   @{FG shine}----------------------------
      USAGE OF MAXMENU PREFS
  ------------------------------@{FG text}


   On the main window you are presented with a:

      Font          - select font to be used on menus and items (really)
      Wind. Pos.    - determine position of MaxMenu window
      Button size   - H+ - height in pixels which will be added to menu
                           buttons
                    - W+ - width in pixels which will be added to menu
                           buttons

      Add           - add new menu
      Edit          - edit menu
      Remove        - remove menu
      Up            - moves menu up
      Down          - moves menu down

      SAVE          - save changes on disk
      USE           - use changes
      CANCEL        - forget the changes


   the next window is almost the same ...

   the edit item window:

      Name          - item name
      Type          - choose the filetype
      File          - executable file
      Arguments     - arguments to be used with file
      Immediately close subwindow -> if it`s turned on the subwindow on
                      MaxMenu will close immediately after executing
                      command



   @{FG shine}----------------------
      USAGE OF MAXMENU
  ------------------------@{FG text}


   Supported keys:

      'q' or 'Q' - Quits MaxMenu

      'r' or 'R' - Refreshs MaxMenu window
@endnode

